data.name: Mushroom and Pea Pesto Pasta
data.quickTastyDescription: A delightful blend of earthy mushrooms and sweet peas tossed in a vibrant pesto sauce, perfect for a quick and satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add the pasta and cook according to package instructions until al dente.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add sliced mushrooms and saut√© until golden brown, about 5-7 minutes.
Stir in the frozen peas and cook for another 2-3 minutes until heated through.
Drain the pasta, reserving a cup of pasta water.
Add the cooked pasta to the skillet with mushrooms and peas. Stir in the pesto sauce, mixing well to coat. If needed, add reserved pasta water for desired consistency.
Serve warm, topped with grated Parmesan cheese, and season with salt and black pepper to taste.
